\title{Endomorphism ring}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-18}
\taxon{example}
\MML{lmod_xx1}{def 9}{K10}

\p{Let #{A} be an additive [[gr-000J]]. Then the set #{\End(A)} of group morphisms ("endomorphisms") #{f\colon A\to A} is a ring.}
\p{We see #{(f+g)(x)=f(x)+g(x)} and #{(f\star g)(x)=(f\circ g)(x)=f(g(x))} are the binary operators for the ring.}
\p{This is called the \define{Endomorphism Ring} of #{A}.}